[233.944155, "o", "## Summary\r\n\r\nI've successfully completed all the requested tasks for creating a web scraper for book information:\r\n\r\n### ✅ Tasks Completed:\r\n\r\n1. **Created Python scraper script** (`/app/scraper_local.py`)\r\n   - Uses BeautifulSoup to parse HTML\r\n   - Extracts title, author, year, rating, and price from book elements\r\n   - Handles the specified HTML structure with proper regex parsing\r\n\r\n2. **Scraped data and saved to CSV** (`/app/books.csv`)\r\n   - Successfully extracted 10 books from the test HTML file\r\n   - CSV contains all required columns: title, author, year, rating, price\r\n   - Data is properly formatted and cleaned (removed \"by \" prefix from authors, parsed numeric values)\r\n\r\n3. **Generated summary report** (`/app/report.txt`)\r\n   - Total books scraped: 10\r\n   - Average book price: $13.84\r\n   - Highest rated book: \"The Hobbit\" by J.R.R. Tolkien (4.9/5 rating)\r\n\r\n### 📊 Results:\r\n\r\nThe scraper extracted data from 10 classic books including:\r\n- The Great Gatsby (1925) - $12.99\r\n- To Kill a Mockingbir"]
[233.944337, "o", "d (1960) - $14.50\r\n- 1984 (1949) - $11.99\r\n- Pride and Prejudice (1813) - $9.99\r\n- And 6 more books...\r\n\r\nAll output files have been saved to the correct locations:\r\n- `/app/books.csv` - 482 bytes\r\n- `/app/report.txt` - 247 bytes\r\n"]
[234.007931, "o", "\u001b[?2004hroot@4dd5cfebb0d1:/app# "]
